= SDL_SoftStretch =
Use this function to perform a fast, low quality, stretch blit between two surfaces of the same pixel format.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_SoftStretch(SDL_Surface*    src,
                    const SDL_Rect* srcrect,
                    SDL_Surface*    dst,
                    const SDL_Rect* dstrect)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''src'''
|the [[SDL_Surface]] structure containing '''srcrect''' / the source rectangle
|-
|'''srcrect'''
|the [[SDL_Rect]] structure representing the source rectangle
|-
|'''dst'''
|the [[SDL_Surface]] structure containing '''dstrect''' / the destination rectangle
|-
|'''dstrect'''
|the [[SDL_Rect]] structure representing the rectangle to be filled with/by the blit
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success or a negative error code on failure; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

